*Rider Verification*


Until now, rider verification was fragmented across the dashboard and the
rider app, with unclear ownership, inconsistent status visibility, and a
manual entry loophole that allowed admins to enter rider documents
themselves.

Introducing rider verification directly within the Rider App, enabling
riders to complete Aadhaar, Driving License and Bank verification from the
Rider App, with real-time status sync on dashboard.
What changes for you

On Dashboard

   -

   Rider creation simplified, admins enter only identity, contact, and
   address
   -

   Setup verification requirements based on your business needs.



   -

   "Pending Invites" tab is renamed to "Pending Verification".
   -

   When document verification is enabled, riders automatically move to the
   "Pending Verification" tab until their documents are verified.
   -

   Riders already on Shift will not be impacted upon enablement
   -

   If verification is enabled, rider will not be able to login to new shift
   until all necessary documents are verified



   -

   Aadhaar is DigiLocker verified, and the bank is verified via penny drop
   -

   Admin control the manual verification flow with Approve and Reject (with
   reason selection), plus Revoke for verified documents and Re-Initiate fo=
r
   rejected ones

[image: pendinf verification page.png]

On Rider App

   -

   Rider profile section, available in the hamburger menu, allows riders to
   view all their details and verified/unverified documents in one place.
   -

   Riders can complete verification from the Profile even when the business
   has disabled it



   -

   Aadhaar verification via DigiLocker, Driving License verification via
   document upload, and Bank verification via Penny drop.
   -

   Manual upload is available as a fallback for Aadhaar verification once
   DigiLocker attempts are exhausted.

What This Means For You



   -

   No change in operational flow upon feature release
   -

   Verification is mandatory for new shifts when enabled
   -

   Riders can complete KYC, Driving License and Bank verification in
   advance from the rider app's profile section, even if verification is no=
t
   mandatory
   -

   If KYC is required, riders can finish ongoing and pending tasks in the
   current shift but cannot log in to the next shift until all enabled
   documents are verified.
   -

   Riders deployed in other businesses must follow those businesses'
   guidelines. If the Requirements are stricter, the rider would only be ab=
le
   to log in once all necessary documents are verified.

What's the Impact


Rider KYC verification helps businesses build a trusted and accountable
workforce, reducing operational risk and compliance exposure. It also
strengthens customer confidence and creates a more scalable foundation for
sustainable growth.


What=E2=80=99s Next

Something exciting is coming soon - Stay tuned !!
